{
  "texts": [
    "Inspired by Jindal and Liu, many heuristic methods have been proposed.",
    "The features widely used in the FRD can be divided into (1) review centric, (2) reviewer centric, (3) metadata centric, and (4) product centric 7.",
    "Review-centric features are the most commonly used features in FRD models and involve the classification and summarization of opinions via psychological analysis, natural language processing (NLP) and data mining.",
    "Reference 8 is one of the first empirical studies on the relationship between psychological suggestion and fake reviews and identifies fake reviews on the basis of psychological cues, time distance, and reviewer location.",
    "Wang et al."
  ]
}